{"id":157750,"global_id":"Z2lkOi8vaGFja2Vyb25lL1JlcG9ydC8xNTc3NTA=","url":"https://hackerone.com/reports/157750","title":"Missing rate limit on critical user actions e.g. reset password, change email, disable account.","state":"Closed","substate":"resolved","readable_substate":"Resolved","created_at":"2016-08-09T03:33:15.107Z","submitted_at":"2016-08-09T03:33:15.107Z","is_member_of_team?":false,"reporter":{"disabled":false,"username":"rohitdua","url":"/rohitdua","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"is_me?":false,"cleared":false,"hackerone_triager":false,"hacker_mediation":false},"team":{"id":13,"url":"https://hackerone.com/security","handle":"security","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/000/013/fa942b9b1cbf4faf37482bf68458e1195aab9c02_original.png/43e4513b9104ea0d68c9c096cea374ba8440dde3e027af5465c8771e8839a67c","medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/000/013/fa942b9b1cbf4faf37482bf68458e1195aab9c02_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"permissions":[],"submission_state":"open","default_currency":"usd","awards_miles":false,"offers_bounties":true,"state":"public_mode","only_cleared_hackers":false,"pentest_feature_enabled?":false,"profile":{"name":"HackerOne","twitter_handle":"Hacker0x01","website":"https://hackerone.com","about":"Vulnerability disclosure should be safe, transparent, and rewarding."}},"has_bounty?":false,"in_validation?":false,"rejected_anc_report_that_can_be_sent_back_to_anc_triagers?":false,"can_view_team":true,"can_view_report":true,"is_external_bug":false,"is_published":false,"is_participant":false,"has_collaborators":false,"stage":4,"public":true,"visibility":"full","cve_ids":[],"singular_disclosure_disabled":false,"disclosed_at":"2019-04-11T18:20:39.979Z","bug_reporter_agreed_on_going_public_at":null,"team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2019-04-11T18:13:55.823Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"Hi\n\nI found that there are no rate limitations present on actions that require a password inside the account settings.\nActions:\n[Paypal email change](https://hackerone.com/settings/bounties)\n[Account email change](https://hackerone.com/settings/email/edit)\n[Password Change](https://hackerone.com/settings/pass/edit)\n[Disable Account](https://hackerone.com/settings/disable) *(this will not be useful to attacker)*\n\nThese sensitive actions require additional verification of password so as to protect the user even if the account is left open and is accessed by an attacker.\nThe attacker can try the dictionary attack *(or infinite wild guessing)*  with multiple threads on password on any of these actions without getting rate limited or locked out.","weakness":{"id":75,"name":"Privilege Escalation"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2019-05-11T18:13:55.978Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-76361567.35256498,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":12,"voters":["ali","rohitdua","japz","sa1tama0","zodiac_tn","nigba","armansameer","dyabla","phoneutria","mohamedreda3870712","and 2 more..."],"structured_scope":{"databaseId":3,"asset_type":"URL","asset_identifier":"https://hackerone.com","max_severity":"critical"},"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"activities":[{"id":1114213,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Instead of locking or time limiting a neat solution could be that the user is automatically logged out after n wrong tries.\nSo a real user could continue after logging again, or use forgot password in other case.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-08-09T06:30:39.027Z","updated_at":"2016-08-09T06:30:39.027Z","actor":{"username":"rohitdua","cleared":false,"url":"/rohitdua","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1114915,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hey @rohitdua,\n\nAlthough the attack you describe requires a pretty big **if** (account access), I think you may have a point here. Usually vulnerabilities that require full account access of your victim are pretty uninteresting, since at that point you can get pretty much all you want. For example, changing the email address is pretty inconsequential, since you already have access to the entire account. The lack of rate-limiting however may allow you to pivot your access to other services for which the user uses the same password, which might make it eligible. \n\nPlease give me some time while I discuss this with my colleagues, we'll get back to you soon!\n\nKind regards,\n@dirk","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-08-09T14:45:55.755Z","updated_at":"2016-08-09T14:45:55.755Z","actor":{"username":"dirk","cleared":false,"url":"/dirk","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/013/067/f9785240873663ec965b04e725871ed0f69616e7_original.jpeg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":true},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1118932,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugNeedsMoreInfo","message":"Hey @rohitdua,\n\nIt looks like we *do* limit password resets to about 1 per 10 seconds per account. Could you please provide me with a PoC that shows that you can exceed this limit? For a successful brute-force attack, you would need a much higher rate than that. \n\nKind regards,\nDirk","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-08-11T09:42:49.325Z","updated_at":"2016-08-11T09:42:49.325Z","actor":{"username":"dirk","cleared":false,"url":"/dirk","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/013/067/f9785240873663ec965b04e725871ed0f69616e7_original.jpeg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":true},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1119125,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugNew","message":"Hi\n\nThere does seem to be a limit on POST requests (password/email/payment/disable) but it seems to be working with nearly 1/second(maybe greater). \nAnd this limit only seems to limited to IP and not to the account or session keys.\nI tried wfuzz in one machine and started getting 429 after few requests. At the same time on another machine(IP) I was able to successfully POST without getting 'Retry Later'.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-08-11T11:30:29.949Z","updated_at":"2016-08-11T11:30:29.949Z","actor":{"username":"rohitdua","cleared":false,"url":"/rohitdua","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1119290,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hey @rohitdua,\n\nApologies, you are correct. I was misreading a rate-limiting rule that applies to our password reset, but doesn't apply to our password change form!","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-08-11T13:13:26.355Z","updated_at":"2016-08-11T13:13:26.355Z","actor":{"username":"dirk","cleared":false,"ur